# ── Build artifacts ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These are produced by `mvn package` inside the build stage — never
# copy them in from the host (saves bandwidth + avoids stale jars).
# EXCEPT .docker-maven/ which contains the Maven runtime jars we need
# to COPY into the build stage (see Dockerfile).
**/target/
**/build/
**/out/
**/*.class
**/*.jar
!/.docker-maven/**/*.jar

# ── Test-only module ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# rag-test is a sibling module consumed only by `mvn verify`. We still
# COPY it into the build context because Maven needs the module dir to
# exist at POM-parse time (parent pom lists <module>rag-test</module>).
# It's then excluded from the reactor via `-pl rag-app,!rag-test`.

# ── IDE / OS junk ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml
*.ipr
*.iws
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ── VCS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# (Uncomment the next line if your .git is huge — usually it isn't.)
# .git/

# ── Secrets / local env ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CRITICAL — never bake credentials into an image layer.
.env
.env.local
.env.*
**/.env
**/.env.*

# ── Runtime artifacts ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
logs/
nohup.out
.hermes/
.agents/

# ── Documentation that bloats context ───────────────────────────────────
# Keep these out of the image build context. They live in git for humans,
# not for the build.
docs/LESSONS.md
docs/plans/
docs/superpowers/
docs/RUNBOOK.md
docs/README.md
README.md

# ── Docker self-references ───────────────────────────────────────────────
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose.yml
.docker/